analysis: The agent included an extra argument ("include_legal_requirements") in its function call that was not expected, causing a mismatch with the required parameters for the ExportRegulationAdvisor tool.
The agent included an extra unsupported parameter "include_trending_colors" in the function call arguments, causing a mismatch with the expected function signature and leading to evaluation failure.
The agent omitted the required "work_focus" parameter in the function call, resulting in a mismatch with the expected signature and thus failure to produce a valid function call.

The agent failed to make any function/tool call, responding only in natural language with options and clarifying questions, instead of directly invoking the appropriate email-sending function as required by the task.

The agent incorrectly included the "provide_indoor_options" parameter, which was not expected or required for the HikingWeatherAdvisor tool call. The parameters did not exactly match the expected function signature, causing the evaluator to reject the call.

The model incorrectly included the "include_graphical_analysis" argument in the TaxPolicyImpactSimulator function call, which is not supported by the tool's defined parameters, resulting in a non-matching function call.

The agent failed to include the explicit phrase "document with" in the "training_routine_data" parameter value, instead paraphrasing it. This mismatch prevented the function call from exactly matching the expected parameters as required by the evaluation.

The agent included an extra unsupported parameter ("include_demographic_info") in its function call to AudienceSegmentationTool, causing the call to not match the expected signature and resulting in evaluation failure.

The agent added an unsupported argument include_weekend_rules to the DailyTrafficRuleNotifier function call, resulting in a parameter mismatch and no valid function call being recognized by the evaluator. Only area_code was expected.

The agent incorrectly set the analysis inclusion flags (include_age_group_analysis, include_location_analysis, include_device_usage) to true, whereas the expected call required all these flags to be false. The root cause is misinterpreting or overlooking default or required parameter values.

The agent included extra unsupported parameters ("include_population_estimates" and "data_format") in the function call, which do not match the defined signature of OceanicBiodiversityData_fetch, resulting in a mismatch with expected valid calls.

The agent used "Amazon_rainforest" instead of the required "Amazon rainforest" for the area_identifier parameter, causing a mismatch with the expected function call and resulting in failure to meet the strict parameter formatting requirement.

The agent used "young adults" as the audience_data instead of the expected "young adult demographic," causing a mismatch with the strict parameter value required by the evaluator. This led to a failure in recognizing the function call despite correct tool use otherwise.

The agent incorrectly capitalized the "industry" parameter value as "Technology" instead of the required lowercase "technology," resulting in a parameter mismatch that caused the evaluator to reject the function call.
